      <prefercite id="ref1">
         <head>Cite As</head>
         <p>Elwyn LaVerne Simons Archives, Vertebrate Paleontology, Yale Peabody Museum</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="ref2">
         <head>Biographical Sketch</head>
         <p>Simons, Elwyn LaVerne. (b. July 14, 1930) BS Rice University 1953, MA Princeton 1955, PhD Princeton1956, DPhil Oxford 1959. Visiting Curator Vert. Paleo. 1960-61; Assoc. Cur. Vert. Paleo. 61-64, Curator Vert. Paleo. 64-77. Elwyn left Yale in 1977 for a professorship at Duke University. Elwyn, a world-renowned specialist on the evolution of fossil primates, is a member of the National Academy of Sciences</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="ref4">
         <head>Description of the Material</head>
         <p>The archives of Elwyn LaVerne Simons include field notes, coresspondence, and manuscript materials all relating to the Yale collection.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
